verbose_text: However, laboratory tests do not seem to have similar results between the cases which were reported; for example, some have reported normal blood lactate and ammonia levels,15 which is similar to our study, while others reported elevated blood lactate.5 According to Reuter et al, RC enzymes were at borderline in skeletal muscle and diagnosis was confirmed by WES (homozygous one-base-pair insertion in HIBCH) 10; similarly in the present case, that WES was used for final diagnosis.
